Here’s a TekAutomate Steps UI flow to measure the delay between the rising edges of CH1 and CH2 on a Tektronix MSO4/5/6 Series oscilloscope. This uses the query step to read the measurement result after configuring the measurement using write steps.

```json
{
  "steps": [
    {
      "type": "connect",
      "id": "connect_scope",
      "title": "Connect to Oscilloscope"
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_delay_measurement",
      "title": "Set Delay Measurement CH1 to CH2 (Rising Edges)",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUREMENT:MEAS1:TYPE DELAY"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_source1",
      "title": "Set Source 1 to CH1",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUREMENT:MEAS1:SOURCE1 CH1"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_source2",
      "title": "Set Source 2 to CH2",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUREMENT:MEAS1:SOURCE2 CH2"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_edge1",
      "title": "Set Edge 1 to Rising",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUREMENT:MEAS1:EDGE1 RISING"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "write",
      "id": "set_edge2",
      "title": "Set Edge 2 to Rising",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUREMENT:MEAS1:EDGE2 RISING"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "query",
      "id": "query_delay_value",
      "title": "Query Delay Measurement Value",
      "params": {
        "command": "MEASUREMENT:MEAS1:VALUE?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "disconnect",
      "id": "disconnect_scope",
      "title": "Disconnect from Oscilloscope"
    }
  ]
}
```

This flow:
1. Connects to the oscilloscope.
2. Configures a delay measurement from CH1 to CH2, both on rising edges.
3. Queries the measured delay value.
4. Disconnects from the oscilloscope.

You can add steps to save or log the result if needed. Let me know if you want to expand this flow!

